observations.recommendation:
1) Require and supervise the Inventory Committee of the municipality to conduct the inventory on the physical count of its road network and prepare a report thereon;
2) Require the Municipal Accountant to recognize the cost of local roads and its components in their Books of Accounts, and
3) Require the Municipal Engineer to provide the Accountant and the General . Services Office with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects.

We recommended  that Management:
Conduct physical count of agency’s total PPE at least once a year by the Inventory Committee and submit Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment;
Maintain and update Subsidiary Ledger and Property Card for each item;
Put Property Identification Card/Property Tag to each item; and
Prepare Acknowledgment Receipt for Equipment (ARE) each time one is issued to an official or employee.

Initiate measures designed to come up with a Memorandum of Agreement (MOA) with the GSIS defining therein the agreed balance of payables to GSIS, if any, and the terms and conditions in the settlement thereof.  The following steps may help in facilitating reconciliation of records.
a. Secure detailed profile of payables per GSIS records;
b. Reconstruct old GSIS accounts, if necessary, and update records;
c. Reconstruct old personnel profile, if necessary, and update personnel profile;
d. Counter-check GSIS records with the reconstructed and updated accounting and personnel records of the LGU; 
e. Negotiate with the GSIS for any differences that may be noted during counter-checking activity;
f. Enter into a formal agreement with the GSIS in the form of a Memorandum of Agreement (MOA); and
g. Appropriate fund for the settlement of any payables to the GSIS as agreed in the MOA.
